caption: Awesome food excellent service
Brussels Sprout salad is out of this world!!
I love this place! The burger and service is exceptional! I highly recommend.  They have the best burgers in town!!! 😊😊😊❤❤❤

The XXL MAX burger, is pure burger bliss! You can tell this burger, bun and sauce are all made in house! A juicy double stacked burger that is very satisfying. The house made fries or sweet potato fries are also very good. They are following Covid protocols and we sat inside, very clean. Only issue, and why it's not a 5 star is we had really lacking service. However, the burger was killer- so we'll be back for sure!
Burger is fine - pretty good even! But the sugar and cinnamon on fries thing is weird,andi wish an option not to add it was available.
Best shakes and wonderful service!!!!
It was just WOW!  It makes me happy to eat awesome food.  This place is going to be my favorite burger place!
Delicious burger made exactly as I like, and the teens loved the milkshakes. Will be back.

Brilliant burger creations paired with sumptuous shake options for the more mature palate.  That is Maxwell's.  Enjoy a good time with great food and exceptional attention from the staff.  Cleanliness, courtesy, and cuisine; anticipate a great time at Maxwell's.
Great milkshakes and burgers.
Probably the best burger I’ve ever had. Been to many local burger places around the country, and this place takes the cake. Just amazing, juicy and delicious burgers.
Really get place for a casual Friday dinner...the make your own burger with bacon, crispy shallots and cheddar was really good. My favorite part though was the fries dipped in Max sauce!
Delicious! Don't miss their happy hour.
Tasty burgers and fries, wagyu was worth the price...staff very attentive....shakes were awesome,  as well as the Manhattan....they should bury Wags just saying ...
Awesome snickers milkshake! Burger and fries were good too

The best crispy chicken sandwich I've ever had. You wont regret ordering it! Cookies and Cream milkshake, yes please! Awesome presentation, delicious food, fast and friendly service (especially for to-go orders). I'll definitely be back! That Mac N' Cheese has my name on it lol!
Good service and food was delicious and quick.
Burger was good Shake was better Fries were not.
9 of us went there tonight. Every single order of fries ended up in the trash because they were more salt than potatoe. Burgers were fine.

My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed our dining experience at Maxwells. We both agree that they make the best burgers in Frederick, the best we’ve ever had period.  Maxwells touts itself as a restaurant that makes everything in house, from the cheese to the beet burgers to the incredible MAX sauce. You can definitely taste the difference!  The service was superb, prompt, polite and fun. Their covid protocols were excellent and their ordering process easy. Even though we opted to order online, our waiter was still attentive and friendly. I highly recommend Maxwells to anyone wanting a delicious meal at a fair price!
The Wagu burger was alright but the fries were great!

Limited menu, the food was good but overpriced. Confused that the "Maxx burger" is 12.95 and has two patties, but a single patty burger is 13.95 because it's considered a "build your own". I ended up getting a chicken sandwich instead which was ok.

Amazing burgers and shakes in downtown Frederick.  They were juicy, thick, and flavorful.  The shakes were like artwork.  Nice touch with the sprinkles of crushed oreos or nutter butter cookie (depending on your shake).  Parking is easy at the Carrol Creek Garage or off street too.
Burger and fries are fantastic.  The service was perfect and waitstaff super courteous and knowledgeable of their menu and ingredients.
Incredibly good burgers! And the sweet potatoe fries are amazing too.
Always quality.
Good burguers and great milkshakes
Pleasant staff, easy ordering and great food
Brussel sprouts salad with chicken was great. Can't wait to try wagyu burger next visit. So glad you are open again, missed coming here.
Stopped in for lunch and fell in love! Wagyu burger and sweet potato fries were everything I never knew I needed. Homemade bread and cheese? PLUS adult milkshakes? Found my new go to place!
I didn’t even know this place existed, and after experiencing the absolute magical burger I had today, I think this is going to be my new lunch spot downtown.
Lovely service and food. Was surprised to have to order at the counter and sit but didn't mind it at all. They bring you the food when it's ready.
What a great menu! The food was creative and it was fun to order a variety to share with friends.
Excellent  cuisine they  are giving food with the restaurant week pricing
Staff is great
The service was great and the food was good.
ABSOLUTE BEST food in Frederick!!! Welcoming atmosphere, top of the line menu, incredible customer service. Can’t wait to come back for Mardi Gras!
Small establishment with the good food,  atmosphere and decor. A little chilly in the cold weather. Best biscuits I've ever had for brunch. Good coffee.

Had a great Valentine's day dinner here. Wonderful small place with delicious food and friendly staff. They had turtle soup which was new to me and absolutely fantastic. A great Louisiana flavor. Jambalaya fritters were tasty as well. Mussels were pretty good but not too different from other places. Steak was cooked perfectly. The vday dessert was butterscotch chocolate lava cake which was one of the best things I've ever had. Add it to the regular menu!
Absolutely delicious! Food was awesome!!!  Great atmosphere with views of Patrick St. Downtown.  Wonderful manager and staff.  We will definitely be coming there again.  Highly recommended 😎
Excellent!!!  5 star quisine!!!
Great food and friendly service.

Our group stopped in for lunch and ordered a slew of things. Each was PHENOMENAL. It’s a warm, welcoming spot, unpretentious but stylish, and they served us quickly. We were blown away by their Brussels sprouts, and the carmelized onion and gruyere grilled cheese. Their fries were impeccably seasoned, crispy and fresh.  We will be back!

Went to Maxwell's tonight for a romantic 5 course New Year's Eve meal and it did not include a single vegetable. And no, I do not consider the 10 French fries served during the 3rd course a  vegetable. Ever heard of brussel sprouts or asparagus? A little broccoli maybe? And for $75 a person, I expected a whole filet. Who serves half a 5 oz filet and calls that a course?
Wonderful service, great prices, and everything is delicious! Their Brussel sprout salad is to die for! Fast too!
Delicious lunch!  Fries were seasoned and French onion grilled cheese and potato soup were divine!

Don't let the ordering at the counter disuaede you from giving it a try! The food impreses in it's preparation, tastes, and choices. Grilled quail and a take on duck a l'orange were both excellent. Not dishes one expects ordering at a counter!

This friendly Frederick restaurant is a fantastic find for delicious food & attentive service. The chef raises the bar for his tasty, mouth watering masterpieces! He designs to the T for his presentations! A few favorites of ours are the Beet & Celery Root Purée Salad, the Crispy Brussel Sprouts & Citrus Salad, the perfectly cooked Trout Almandine, the tender & juicy Steak Frites, the Crispy Duck Breast, the Coq Au Vin.. I could go on & on!! An excellent dining experience and it gets better every time we go there .. the food is Absolutely Amazing! Each course exceeded our expectations and it’s our favorite restaurant!
Great food but pricey.
French onion grilled cheese my favorite. Nice spot 👍🏽
The only thing not excellent about this place is the music. Definitely come check it out.
Brussel sprouts are amazing. They don’t have as many vegan options as they used to. Quick quality food
Staff was friendly and the impossible burger was good.  Fries were very good.
I had the CHICKEN PO' BOY SANDWICH and I’m sorry it had a funny taste :-(  My husband ordered the burger sandwich and it was much better than what I ordered, the fries were tasty.
Loved it

Fast service, and excellent food! The popcorn and fries are seasoned to perfection (maybe herbs de Provence?)! Get there early if you want their ants on a log, because it's one of their best dishes! Cocktails are based on local spirits (literally next door), and top notch. Staff has always been super, too.
Yum! Filling and tasty. If your dish comes with the herbed french fries, do try them with the 504 sauce instead of ketchup. Definitely worth a visit!
excellent service, great fresh food
Maxwell's is a must see when visiting Fredrick, the chef is absolutely wonderful, and the menu is delicious. They offer local brews and dishes that cater to the local industries.
Loved everything I ate! I like the self serve idea, but it's a little confusing as a first time visitor. Definitely going back.

Service was ok. We weren't told about the specials. The tea was maybe hibiscus which we were not told about and didn't enjoy. Way too many fries with the frites. The beignets were not good and came with a coffee flavored cream on it which was not obvious to us and we don't like coffee. First time so maybe we'll try it again but it's a big maybe.
This place was the BOMB. Cant best their lunch special burger berr and fries for 7 bucks
Came here expecting wonderful food and for okay food.  A cool spot but maybe not worth the money.
Brussel sprouts were a bit overdone but the chicken was good.

Like other's have said the food isn't bad but it isn't really that great compared to other offerings at the current price.  Plus with the added wait and smaller portions without making up for it in quality, it's currently very low on my list of places to swing in for lunch.
Meals were fresh and tasty

The attention to detail is unbelievable!  The staff is top notch.  The food is great...(we got the chicken big-boy and the French onion grilled cheese)!  And I'm not sure I've seen a better "to-go" bag then this!!!
Great food.
Good casual food and atmosphere.  Some tasty vegetarian options.
Good food and atmosphere. Would go back.

Stopped here on first Saturday and we were glad we did! I got the beet sandwich and my husband got the brisket. Both things were great and the fries and fried avocado just made the meal that much better! The beer on tap was ice cold. You order at the counter and they bring you the food. Before you sit down make sure you get your condiments from the side counter! It will save you a trip once your food comes and you realize you do t have them!  We will definitely eat here again!
Cool little dinner with a friendly vibe and good food. Had the brisket and mac n cheese which was awesome.
Gourmet burger and beer special is an unbelievable value!

The atmosphere is nice and the restaurant is well decorated. Good location on Patrick street. The food, however, is just ok. I had the marinated chicken with a side salad. The sandwich was drenched with the special sauce which was not that flavorful and took away from the flavor of the chicken. The salad was also dressed to heavily with the vinaigrette; despite that I was pleased that it was a real salad not just iceberg and shredded carrots. My husband had the burger and fries which he thought was ok. The burger looked very juicy the fries however were not fresh so you could barely taste the garlic and vinegar. I'm  not sure about giving Maxwell's Kitchen a second chance.
The food was not what we were expecting from a restaurant connected with the Wine Kitchen. We were hoping for the same level of freshness and quality and left very unimpressed.

The food isn’t bad,  but for the price there are too many better options in downtown Frederick.  Ordering at the counter is a challenge because there isn’t a board with the menu. You have to read one of two menus at the counter when you get to the front of the line.  You order at the counter and get your own fountain drink and condiments, so why is there a call button on the tables?
Great new restaurant! Food was great! Nice people, nice atmosphere. Really like this place.
Great addition to the food scene. Quick place to get a bite to eat on a Sunday night. Food came out about 10 minutes and it was yummy!
Food here is amazing. Excellent choices and easygoing vibe. Great people watching from bay window on Patrick street.  Quick and easy but high quality, delicious food.
Upscale fast food.  Decent for the price.
Nice place in downtown Frederick. Not a huge menu, but interesting choices. Really enjoyed the food there.
Poké bowl was fantastic!
Very healthy choices. The beatstrami was absolutely delicious. Nice atmosphere and vibe!!

The food was very good, slightly overpriced in my mind, but still very good. We had a Pinot Noir by Joe's (house wine) and a malbec. Both tasted, well, cheap. I didn't like either of them. Still more wine to try, but I sincerely hope they broaden the menu; I thought it was not that expansive.
Great food for a quick meal with beer or wine.  Soda and ice cream are flavorful
We enjoyed the Kung Pao jackfruit, curry cauliflower bites, and fried avocado.
Love this new addition to downtown Frederick! The chicken sandwich is sooo good! The 504 sauce is a must with the fries. Service was thorough and speedy. Definitely recommend ❤️
If you haven't tried Maxwell's on East Patrick you got to go amazing recommended by the Frederick magazine
Staff is friendly , food is delicious!
Great food, service, decor and atmosphere.  The Crab Cake Sandwich and fries were excellent.  This will be my go to lunch place every time I visit Frederick!

Second time back and just as good as the first.  Greeted by smiling faces and an open kitchen. It's a quaint counter order spot that is representative of it's fast casual menu.  I've ordered the chicken confit leg jambalaya twice now as well as the double stack with house made brioche and tomato jam.  Chef is from New Orleans and he brought the jambalaya with him.  Will return time and time again, great new spot in Frederick.
Amazing food, totally worth the price.
Great new addition to downtown Frederick. Service has been consistently great, and the food is always excellent.

Absolutely loved it and glad it's open to enjoy! The food was amazing, I highly recommend the fried avocado. The staff couldn't have been nicer and the service was great! Will be adding this to our lunch rotation at work for sure! Can't wait to go back!

First, greeting by a smiling staff (one of whom complimented my Phantasm shirt!) We ordered the double stack, fries, cauliflower nuggets and the carrot coconut soup. Each item was fantastic and very reasonably priced! With a courteous, attentive staff and a small and delicious menu this place is going to thrive. Recommend anyone and everyone hit this place and it veg friendly. Oh yeah, try the sauce.

Super cool place. Very innovative and unique menu, I even tried a few vegan dishes and I’m not even vegan but they were SO delicious! Looking forward to trying more of the menu soon. Super friendly staff too, excited to have a fast yet healthy choice in downtown!
